medical_history.chief_complaint: Multiple erythematous, crusted, eroded papules on the dorsal aspects of the hands and lesions on the face.
medical_history.history_of_present_illness: The lesions were painful, pruritic, nonhemorrhagic, and had been present for 1 month. Initially, the rash was thought to be consistent with impetigo. Existing lesions partially improved with treatment but did not resolve, and new lesions developed on the face and eyelids. After removal of an etonogestrel implant placed 4 months prior, the patient reported substantial improvement in her cutaneous symptoms over the next month.
medical_history.past_medical_history: The patient has a nonsignificant past medical history. She denied any acute porphyria symptoms.
medical_history.family_history: She has no known family history of porphyria.
